HoboSerenity
============

This plugin tries to simplify the process of integrating two great gems: Hobo and Serenity-ODT. It also uses a Python Script to convert the reports to PDF using OpenOffice.

Thanks to:

* https://github.com/kremso/serenity
* http://www.artofsolving.com/opensource/pyodconverter


Requirements
============

* Rails 2.3.8
* Hobo 1.0.1 gem
* Serenity-odt gem
* Git
* OpenOffice in server mode (listening on localhost:8100)


Installation
============

script/plugin install git://github.com/iox/hobo-serenity.git



How to use
==========

First step, a couple of global variable en config/environment.rb. ODT_PATH is the folder in which documents will be saved, and KEEP_ODT ensures ODTs are kept in the filesystem after PDF creation.
  # HoboSerenity configuration options
  ODT_PATH = 'documentos/'
  KEEP_ODT = true
  
  
Second step, define the templates and file names you are going to use. The name of the method is the template name, and the string it returns the name of the document you are going to create (without .odt or .pdf).
  # --- Document creation --- #
  def example
    "DOC-" + id.to_s
  end
  
  
Third step, add download methods to the controller
  #Allow File Downloads
  include HoboSerenityController
  
  
And finally, add the download buttons to the view:
 <show-page>
  <append-heading:>
    <a href="&this.odt_download_path('example')" class="button">Download ODT</a>
    <a href="&this.pdf_download_path('example')" class="button">Download PDF</a>
  </append-heading:>
 </show-page>
    
    
    
    
